headline: Ulta Beauty, Rubrik, Docusign: 3 companies beating estimates
summary: Morning Brief hosts Seana Smith and Madison Mills take a closer look at several trending stocks: Ulta Beauty (ULTA) shares are jumping by over 12% on the cosmetic brand's third quarter earnings beat. Rubrik (RBRK) also beat on its latest earnings print, while also raising its full-year guidance as analysts cite strong demand for data security. As part of its latest earnings results, Docusign (DOCU) saw its sales grow by 9% year-over-year for its third quarter. headline: Ulta Beauty Stock Eyes Biggest Gain in 2 Years. It’s Still Inexpensive.
summary: Ulta Beauty  stock jumped after management raised its forecast for full-year earnings, but doubt about the long-term story has kept a lid on the valuation.  On Thursday after the market closed, Ulta reported sales of $2.53 billion and $5.14 in earnings per share for its third fiscal quarter, the three months that ended Nov. 2.  The consensus calls among analysts tracked by  FactSet  was for $4.53 in earnings per share and $2.5 billion in sales.
